# world/cocoaui.list — the conditional Cocoa GUI world layer
# (docs/cocoa_gui_design.md §12.3, sprint_cocoa_gui.md CG1). Loaded ONLY by
# the UI worker via `frontend::world::load_list(vm, path)` AFTER the base
# world is up — never from world/world.list, so the CLI, the WKWebView GUI,
# and the base test suite carry none of it.
#
# Same format as world.list: one .mst path per line, relative to THIS file's
# directory; blank lines and #-comments skipped. Files reserved 63+ (01-62 are
# taken by the base world; verify with `ls world/`).
63_cocoaui_stub.mst
# MacvmDelegate (the C6 delegate/action-target registry) loads BEFORE CocoaUI:
# CG4's `CocoaUI startup` references `MacvmDelegate actionTargetOn:` for the
# Workspace ⌘P/⌘D target, so the class must be declared when 64 compiles. The
# list order — not the filename number — is what fixes the forward reference.
65_cocoadelegate.mst
64_cocoaui.mst
# CocoaBrowser (CG7) loads after CocoaUI: startup resolves it BY NAME and asks
# it to register its view, so the file is optional — remove the line and the
# shell simply has no Browser entry.
66_cocoabrowser.mst
67_cocoafind.mst
# CocoaEditor (the class text editor tab) also self-registers by name:
# native NSTextView editing; Save recompiles live on the primary (uiDoit) +
# persists the diff to the image + world (host).
68_cocoaeditor.mst
# CocoaOutliner (the Strongtalk-style unfolding tree, LIVE ClassMirror
# reflection — the other half of the dual placement from CocoaBrowser's DB
# queries) also self-registers by name.
69_cocoaoutliner.mst
# CocoaCanvas (an RGBA drawing surface — pixel buffer + vector command batch,
# docs/CANVAS.md) also self-registers; needs 66 (CocoaBrowser hostService).
70_cocoacanvas.mst
# CocoaHelp (a read-only Markdown documentation tab, docs/macvm_help.md)
# also self-registers by name; no dependency on any other Cocoa GUI file.
71_cocoahelp.mst
# CocoaBrowser2 (V2, additive — V1's 66_cocoabrowser stays): a classic
# Smalltalk-80 category browser — system-category / class / protocol / method
# panes (categories from the M1 package lists, protocols derived heuristically
# from selectors) + a Comment/Definition/Source pane. Read-only browsing;
# self-registers by name as the 'Browser V2' view.
72_cocoabrowser2.mst
